Integrate Data into CRM Analytics Datasets

Use the upload user interface to create a single dataset based on external .csv data. To refresh the data, you can overwrite the data in the dataset by uploading a new .csv file.

When CRM Analytics loads any data into a dataset, it also adds metadata about each column of data. When you upload a .csv file, CRM Analytics infers metadata about each column in the file.

You can specify the metadata in a metadata file. A metadata file is a JSON file that describes the structure of an external data file. After you create a dataset based on an external data file, you can edit the dataset to apply a new metadata file.

Upload a CSV File to Create a Dataset
You can upload external data in a .csv format through the user interface. When you upload a .csv file, CRM Analytics infers the metadata about each column in the .csv file.

Rules for Automatic Generation of a Metadata File
When you upload a CSV file from the user interface, Analytics automatically generates the metadata file as long as the CSV file meets certain requirements.

Monitor an External Data Upload
When you upload an external data file, CRM Analytics kicks off a job that uploads the data into the specified dataset. You can use the Monitor tab of the data manager to monitor and troubleshoot the upload job.

Set a Source Time Zone for .CSV Data
